<BaseLayout title="About" description="Stepan Zolotukhin — building ZINC, an LLM inference engine for AMD consumer GPUs with Zig and Vulkan compute.">
  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>I'm Stepan Zolotukhin. I build systems software with a focus on GPU computing and AI infrastructure.</p>

  <p>My current project is <a href="/zinc">ZINC</a> — an LLM inference engine written in Zig with Vulkan compute shaders, targeting AMD RDNA3/RDNA4 consumer GPUs that mainstream AI stacks ignore. The goal is to make a $500 GPU as useful for local LLM inference as hardware that costs 30x more.</p>

  <p>I write about the work on this site — GPU kernel optimization, Vulkan compute, quantization algorithms, systems engineering tradeoffs, and what it takes to build performance-critical software from scratch.</p>

